Another way to think about it is using the unit circle. The unit circle has points (cos θ, sin θ). So, if I have a point (0, 3), that's 3 times the unit vector pointing straight up. So, the angle θ is still π/2 because scaling doesn't change the angle, only the radius. So, even though r is 3, θ remains π/2.

