3. Break that into two sums: Σ_{n=2}^∞ 1/n² - Σ_{n=2}^∞ 1/n³.

4. Recognize that Σ_{n=2}^∞ 1/n² = p - 1 and Σ_{n=2}^∞ 1/n³ = q - 1.

5. Therefore, S = (p - 1) - (q - 1) = p - q.

