p(4) = 4/(16 - 1) = 4/15 ≈ 0.2667

p(5) = 5/(25 - 1) = 5/24 ≈ 0.2083

p(6) = 6/(36 - 1) = 6/35 ≈ 0.1714

p(7) = 7/(49 - 1) = 7/48 ≈ 0.1458

So, p(x) passes through these six points: (2, 2/3), (3, 3/8), (4, 4/15), (5, 5/24), (6, 6/35), (7, 7/48). Since p(x) is a degree 5 polynomial, and we have six points, that should uniquely determine the polynomial.

