Putting it all together, the prime factors of 242 are 2 × 11 × 11. 

Now, to simplify the square root, I can pair the factors. Each pair of the same prime factor can be taken out of the square root as a single factor. 

So, I have one pair of 11s and one single 2. The pair of 11s can be simplified to 11, and the single 2 remains under the square root. 

Therefore, √242 = √(2 × 11²) = √(11²) × √2 = 11√2.

