So, both methods give me 2000 calories. Hmm, that seems high, but maybe that's just the way it is. Let me think about it. If 2% is 40 calories, then 100% is 2000. So, 2000 calories a day. That's actually the average recommended daily caloric intake for an adult, isn't it? Yeah, I think it's around 2000 calories. So, that seems to make sense.

