To solve the problem, we start by calculating the perimeter of the regular hexagon. A regular hexagon has 6 sides, each with a length of 16 cm. The perimeter of the hexagon is calculated as follows:

\[
\text{Perimeter of hexagon} = 6 \times 16 \, \text{cm} = 96 \, \text{cm}
\]

Since the regular octagon has the same perimeter as the hexagon, we know the perimeter of the octagon is also 96 cm. A regular octagon has 8 sides, so we let \( s \) be the length of each side of the octagon. The perimeter of the octagon is given by:

\[
\text{Perimeter of octagon} = 8 \times s
\]

Setting this equal to the perimeter of the hexagon, we have:

\[
8 \times s = 96 \, \text{cm}
\]

Solving for \( s \), we divide both sides by 8:

\[
s = \frac{96 \, \text{cm}}{8} = 12 \, \text{cm}
\]

Thus, the length of each side of the octagon is \(\boxed{12}\) cm.
