But wait, \( w = z^2 \), so \( z^2 \) is a primitive 3rd root of unity. That means \( z \) must be a 6th root of unity, right? Because if \( w^3 = 1 \), then \( (z^2)^3 = z^6 = 1 \). So, \( z \) must be a 6th root of unity.

